sec.p:
Following the subgroup and univariate meta-regression analyses, a multivariate meta-regression analysis was performed on all response variables to identify the best model that explains the between-study variability in effect size estimates. In the meta-regression, the variable x represents study characteristics (such as region, country, year, sample size, score level and detection method), which are used to predict the study effect size (
θ^k^
) as shown in the following model (Equation 1):(1)θ^k^=θ+βxk+∈k+ζk
